-@title = "#{t('txt.ui.name')} #{t('txt.ui.interactions.draggable.default')} - #{t('txt.ui.interactions.draggable.constrain-movement')}"
= render :partial => "constrain_movement.js.haml", :format => :js
      
.demo
  %h3
    =image_tag("icons/22x22/jquery-ui.png", :border => 0)
    =@title
  %h3.docs
    Constrain movement along an axis:
  #draggable.draggable.ui-widget-content
    %p
      I can be dragged only vertically
  #draggable2.draggable.ui-widget-content
    %p
      I can be dragged only horizontally
  %h3.docs
    Or to within another DOM element:
  #containment-wrapper
    #draggable3.draggable.ui-widget-content
      %p
        I'm contained within the box
    #draggable4.draggable.ui-widget-content
      %p
        I'm contained within the box's parent
    .draggable.ui-widget-content
      %p
        #draggable5.ui-widget-header
          I'm contained within my parent
/ End demo
.demo-description
  %p
    Constrain the movement of each draggable by defining the boundaries of the draggable area. Set the
    %code
      axis
    option to limit the draggable's path to the x- or y-axis, or use the
    %code
      containment
    option to specify a parent DOM element or a jQuery selector, like 'document.'
/ End demo-description
